---
import Feature from '../../layouts/Feature.astro';
---

<Feature
  title="DAEMON MODE"
  subtitle="Planned — persistent sessions, crash recovery, reconnect anytime."
>
  <div class="roadmap-banner">
    <strong>This feature is on the roadmap and not yet implemented.</strong>
    <p>The design is outlined below. See the <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/roadmap`}>roadmap</a> for current status.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Sessions Persist</h2>
  <p>ori-term will separate shell sessions from the window. A background process will keep shells running even when you close the window. Reopen ori-term and pick up exactly where you left off — scrollback, working directories, and all.</p>
  <p>A single-process mode will be available as a fallback for sandboxed environments.</p>

  <h2>Auto-Save</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Layout saved automatically</strong> — Window positions, tabs, pane layout, and working directories saved periodically</li>
    <li><strong>Crash recovery</strong> — Detect unexpected exits on next launch and offer to restore the session</li>
    <li><strong>Safe writes</strong> — Session files written safely to prevent corruption from unexpected shutdowns</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Remote Shells</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SSH</strong> — Open remote shells via SSH with agent forwarding and keepalive</li>
    <li><strong>WSL</strong> — Windows Subsystem for Linux integration with auto-detection</li>
    <li>Run local and remote shells side by side in the same window</li>
  </ul>
</Feature>

<style>
  .roadmap-banner {
    border: var(--border-weight) solid var(--accent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, transparent);
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .roadmap-banner strong {
    color: var(--accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .roadmap-banner p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
